    xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mth="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
    xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <title>Create a
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161009T110123+0200" comment="Who does this task? IMplementer?"?>category<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
    <para>When you have created all category options for a particular category, you can create that
        category.</para>
    <para>To create a category: </para>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open the  <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                    role="bold">Category</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                >Category</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click the add button.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Fill in the form:</para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis></para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis role="bold">Code</emphasis></para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis role="bold">Data dimension type</emphasis></para>
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160622T161804+0200" comment="At next release: rewrite para." flag="done"?>
                    <para>A category either be of type &quot;Disaggregation&quot; or
                        &quot;Attribute&quot;. For disaggregation of data elements, you select
                            <emphasis role="bold">Disaggregation</emphasis>. The data dimension type
                        &quot;Attribute&quot; allows the category to be used to assign a combination
                        of categories to data recorded through a data set.</para>
                    <?oxy_comment_end?>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis role="bold">Data dimension</emphasis></para>
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160622T161850+0200" comment="At next revision:
Reword para." flag="done"?>
                    <para>If you select <emphasis role="bold">Data dimension</emphasis>, the
                        category will be available to the analytics as another dimension, in
                        addition to the standard dimensions of &quot;Period&quot; and
                        &quot;Organisation unit&quot;.</para>
                    <?oxy_comment_end?>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select category options and assign them.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
</section>
